section.section:
The Administrator shall be selected based on criteria adopted by the Board in regulation, which shall include:
the Administrator's proven ability to provide health insurance coverage to individuals;
the efficiency and timeliness of the Administrator's claim processing procedures;
an estimate of total charges for administering the Plan;
the Administrator's proven ability to apply effective cost containment programs and procedures; and
the financial condition and stability of the Administrator.

text.section:
The Administrator shall perform functions relating to the Plan as required by the Board, including:
determination of eligibility;
data collection;
case management;
financial tracking and reporting;
payment of claims; and
premium billing.
